Brasil Foods to Suspend Perdigao Brand in Bid to Win Antitrust Approval

-- B y   F r a n c i s c o   M a r c e l i n o
-- 
2011-07-13T14:43:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-13/brasil-foods-to-suspend-perdigao-brand-in-bid-to-win-antitrust-approval.html
BRF - Brasil Foods SA (BRFS3) ,  Brazil ’s
biggest maker of TV dinners and frozen meat products, would have
to suspend top brand Perdigao for three to five years for some
products under a proposal being considered by Brazil’s antitrust
regulator today.  The company also proposed selling some plants and other
assets and suspending the use of the Batavo brand for all meat
products for four years, Ricardo Ruiz, a commissioner of the
regulator known as Cade, said today at a meeting in Brasilia.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Francisco Marcelino in Sao Paulo at 
 mdeoliveira@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jessica Brice at 
 jbrice1@bloomberg.net  